  "name": "RPlog_Zik_and_Joh_Talk_p1",
  "title": "Old Friends and Ancient Stones",
  "summary": "In the REC Shipyards main bay aboard the OS Paladin, the overworked Sullustan Colonel Enb'Zik takes a rare break atop his starfighter when his old friend, the Jedi pilot Johanna te Danaan, wanders up to shoot the breeze. Over a pot of caf, they reconnect, trading jabs about overwork, restlessness, and the pilot's eagerness to make Imperial ships explode, though Johanna notes an uncharacteristically dark edge to Zik's word choices. When Zik mentions his upcoming mission to investigate ancient stone artifacts with strange writing, possibly Jedi-related, Johanna spits out her drink and sharply warns him to stay out of the affairs of the Dark Side. Pressing him about who assigned the mission and harboring private fears tied to her own visions and the stones on Tatooine and Kashyyyk, she extracts the name of the archaeologist brought aboard by Leia, Kyle Senesca, while Zik calmly insists he only wants to understand what his team may be walking into.",
